benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/emails/{accountEmailId}/auditLogsWithHistory - Retrieve account email audit logs with history by id

covered: Valid Request: TC01 verifies successful retrieval (200) with Content-Type and expected AuditLog fields.
Empty Response: TC02 verifies an existing account email with no audit logs returns an empty JSON array (200).
Error Scenarios: TC03/TC04 validate 404 responses for missing account and missing accountEmail respectively.
Input Validation: TC05/TC06 validate invalid UUID formats returning 400.
Authentication/Authorization Negative Cases: TC07 and TC08 validate missing/invalid auth return 401.
Service-level Errors: TC09 (503) and TC12 (504) cover service unavailable and downstream timeout behavior.
Schema/Contract & Regression: TC16 verifies schema compatibility; TC15 verifies ordering (changeDate desc).
Large Dataset / Performance: TC11 exercises a very large result set and includes a response-time expectation.
Query Parameters: TC10 confirms adding unknown/extra query parameters does not break the endpoint.
Security: TC13 and TC14 include SQL injection and XSS attempt handling (invalid input formats).
State Variations: TC18 and TC19 cover empty and partially populated DB states.
gaps: Pagination: No tests for pagination semantics (page size, page number, offsets, limits) or behavior when results are split across pages. TC11 tests large payload size but not pagination behavior.
Rate Limiting / Throttling: No scenarios to exercise request throttling or expected 429 responses under excessive request rates.
Caching Behavior / Conditional GETs: No tests checking Cache-Control, ETag, Last-Modified headers or conditional GET responses (304 Not Modified).
Authorization scope / Forbidden (403): Tests cover unauthenticated (401) but not authorized-but-forbidden scenarios (403) when credentials are valid but lack permissions.
Server Error (500) and graceful degradation: No explicit tests simulating internal server errors or DB failures resulting in 500 responses and verifying error format.
Response Headers and Metadata: Aside from Content-Type, headers such as Content-Length, pagination-related headers, and retry-after are not verified.
Pagination-related performance and streaming: No tests for server streaming, chunked responses, or how very large payloads are delivered incrementally.
URI encoding and edge-case path handling: No tests for URL-encoded IDs, reserved characters, or very long path segments beyond simple "invalid-format".
recommendations: Add explicit pagination tests: request with page/limit params (if supported) and verify total count, links or headers (next/prev), boundary conditions (last page, page out-of-range).
Introduce rate-limiting tests that send many requests in short intervals to verify 429 responses and retry behavior.
Add caching/conditional-get tests: verify presence and correctness of Cache-Control, ETag, Last-Modified and behavior of If-None-Match / If-Modified-Since (304 responses).
Add authorization-scope tests to validate 403 Forbidden when authenticated users lack required permissions or roles.
Add server-error simulation tests (500) by mocking DB/service failures to ensure consistent error payloads and safe failure modes.
Expand header validations: assert Content-Length, appropriate charset, and any pagination or retry headers the API should expose.
If the service may stream or chunk large responses, add tests for chunked transfer and client consumption; otherwise add tests for acceptable maximum payload size and memory impacts.

Add URI-encoding and edge-case path tests: URL-encoded UUIDs, extremely long IDs, whitespace or reserved characters properly rejected or handled, and verify consistent 400 responses for malformed paths.
